Ever wanted to blow up a petrol station? well now you can!

The layout of this map is final there are a few bugs that need fixing but it is alot of fun to play.

Rounds tend to be short but that is due to the openess of the map, it is a great map for sniping and there are good hiding spots and some great flanking to be had. I would like to add it is especially pleasing seeing somone been blown of the edge of the canyon.

#### **DE_GASOLINE**

Bomb/Defuse CS:S Map by [Av3ris](http://mappingbase.de/members/275-Av3ris) / Marco Wahler.

 Another nice viewed medium sized industrial-themed map with realistic high-detailed environment, good lightning and fascinating gameplay.
Outdoor and indoor areas are half-to-half presented here, and they reproduced a certain Oil Production Complex with some office buildings, underground corridors and two bomb-sites: The Central Control/Server Room (A) and The Drill/Pump Device (B).

 This is a beta, but it is absolutely playable and seems a bugs free. Friendly for mid- and low-range fightings.

 Overview, Radar and some other custom stuff are included in BSP-file. NOTE: NAV-file for Bots are included too, but it seems not hand-tuned (imho).

 Map was taking 2-nd Place in first official Mappingbase.de CS:S Mappingcontest (supported by BFHosting.com and ESL), which has ended October 2011.
 Results of Competition: _http://mappingbase.de/content/151-Contest-Ergebnisse_

 Map was once released Mart 2012 as a part of Mappingbase CS:S Mappingcontest Mappack 1 (Full Version).
 Mappack download page: _http://mappingbase.de/content/255-Mappingbase-Mappack_
 Direct download link: _http://download.gc-gaming.de/bashor/mappingbase/css_maps/Contest_2011_MB_Mappack.zip_

 Thanks for your viewings and feedbacks. Good Frags and Enjoy!

 P.S. Sorry my English, I am from Russia ;-)

GASOLINE

Bomb/Defuse Map for Counter-Strike: Source

Beta version (2011): Av3ris
Final version (2018): Niko
Navigation Mesh: Meurglis3

Here is an final completion of the once unfinished beta version of the fine map for Counter-Strike: Source by Av3ris / Marco Wahler. Beta version of map was taking 2nd place in first official Mappingbase.de CS:S Mappingcontest (has ended October 2011). And now, seven years later, this unfinished beta version was carefully reworked and fully completed!

Another nice viewed medium sized industrial-themed map with realistic high-detailed environment, comfortable lightning and fascinating gameplay. Outdoor and indoor areas are half-to-half presented here, and they reproduced a certain oil refinery location with some service buildings, underground corridors and two bomb-sites. Also the map is absolutely friendly for mid- and low-range fast-paced shootings!

Story:
   Terrorists are launching attack on an Oil Production Complex. Because of regressive production, the station has been nearly abandoned in the last 30 years. It suffers under advancing decay. The Terrorists used several security leaks to enter the Station through the underground. Their ambition is to completely stop the oil extraction and to express there anger about the hated regime... There are two primary objectives: The Central Control- and Server Room (Bombsite A) and The Drill- and Pump Device (Bombsite B).

P.S. ~ There Will Be Blood :-)

After three months in the making, God only knows how many hours, 3 external test builds and 30 something internal builds, it is my pleasure to present my freshmen foray into the world of mapping; de_gallery. My goal was to create something unique, and I believe I have succeeded. This difference is first apparent aesthetically, and is further exemplified in the map's layout and the way it plays. A haven for those who fear (or loathe) sniper rifles, de_gallery's focus on close quarters combat forces players to leave their instagibbing AWPs at home. While relatively small from an orthographic, top-down perspective, the Z axis received a lot of love, which adds excitement to fire-fights and allowed for a plethora of routes to be woven into the map's sequestered confines. This provides the player multiple, viable paths to any given location and allows the clever man (or woman) to outthink an opponent as opposed to simply outgunning him, while still adhearing to a coherent, linear design.

Twas a long, seldom frustrating process, but I learned a lot along the way, and am proud of what I've ended up with. I hope you'll enjoy it. It is good to finally be done.

The map has a lot of variety in its envrionments, and due to the indoor nature of it, it is hard to take screenshots that do the thing justice (it must be seen!), but here are a few more shots;

#### Story:


Operation Gale Crater


Red Planet Gale Crater,
Date: 28.04.2013,


Well men let's remind 20 July 1969, yes our landing at moon surface...
some people laught, some people belive but that is not matthers now. We all know that landing in 1969 was testing
for big operation on mars. After fiew fails we finally land on red planet in october 1989, and this time we didn't
want public atention you know, there will always be theory of conspiracy like our moon landing in 1969.

In our second landing oh man, that was a big operation really big... But this time our goal was base on red planet,
not just landing, that hapends one year after first one, in 1990.
After 4 years, our base start to operate in 1994, but let's get to the point now.


Our curiosity rover II, after daily routine exploring found some object or thing, we dont know jet what was that object
but we know that thing completlly destroy's our rover, the rover was just totally meltet down, only black box survived.
Our team found black box and we linked into our computer in storage area whitch we call A section. For that operation
of reading hemical materies from melted rover, and from black box we called some specialist's form international space 
station.
But instead we get specialist's we got secret agent's or we can call them terorrist's in our base.


But there was one more problem... in the lower part of base in section B we almost finish experiment of white 
energy program, that will provide on earth free energy for all people on earth that will resolve all the problems.
But in this greaddy world that was the problem... someone want to stop our program at all coast.
We must defend this base at all coast, and if we win, we will bring nice and beeter age on earth.

Good luck men.

de\_future\_aztec
==================
After the first terrorist attack a mineral was discovered in the ruins. It's rarity and value caused companies to begin tearing down all the aztec ruins and completely reshaping the landscapes, digging up and mining as much of the mineral as the could out of the earth. Instead of towering aztec temples, now there are just warehouses and industrial buildings used to store and purify the minerals. Now ecoterrorits are coming to end this massacre of the land.

Features:
=========
- A whole new detailed vision of de_aztec
- Completely redone textures/bsp
- Added new paths
- Different environmental feel and look
- Textures from TopHattWaffle and a amazing skybox created by Hip Shot and converted to CSS by Burnfingers
- A custom overview/radar

Created entirely by hand!
=========================
 (metaphorically speaking)
I only copied over the floor sizes in de_aztec and worked from there. The 3D skybox was also copied over.

by V0lK1

NorthernPetrol(TM) has developed the new generation of fuel:
Every barrel of it is produced with less crude oil than every
other fuel. But the competitors already realized their problem
and commissioned a terrorist group to destroy the main refinery
of NP.

Terrorists:
Plant the C4 either on the crude oil tanks (spot A) or the train
terminal (spot B), which is filled with containers of the fuel.

Counter-Terrorists:
Prevent the Terrorists from planting bombs on the premises
of the factory. If they done so, defuse the explosive charges!
